        | mlogger.update("info", "More info", "More info");

//
h4 Params

table.params-table
    tr
        td param
        td type
        td default
        td description
    tr
        td show_stems
        td Boolean
        td true
        td Shows vertical lines joining the entries of the logger
    tr
        td show_timestamp
        td Boolean
        td false
        td Shows a timestamp on each entry
    tr
        td max_length
        td Number
        td 100
        td How many entries are displayed on the logger
    

//
h4 Update

p.
    Call the update method to insert a new entry, specifing the icon, the title and the text

code
    | Subtle.GaugeHistoric.update(icon, title, text, [timestamp = ""], [color = ""])

p.
    The icon can be "info", "warning" or "error". The color parameter is the color of the icon. If
    it's an empty string, it will display the corresponding color from Subtle.COLORS.

